reviews.text: Cost too much and doesn’t taste good. Even at 100% sugar it was barely sweet
Tasty! I tried milk tea. You can adjust sugar and ice
so far the best milk top i have ever tried in hk! and the pearls were chewy. i had 奶霜鐵觀音加蜜香珍珠 and will go back to try its 茶香珍珠 soon!

This is a bubble tea store that seems to specialise in fruit teas. They also sell the regular bubble tea with different selection of tea. I had the Jasmine green tea latte with pearls which costed 30HKD. 

They had options for tea flavoured pearls as well which I did not try.

My initial impression was not too great as the cashier had lots of make up on and looked kinda weird and she wasn't too polite. However, the wait was fast and they made the drinks really quickly! All in all, it took under 5 mins to order and receive my drink.

The drink came in a tall plastic cup and it spills out of the lid very easily as the lid does not fit the cup exactly and is kind of cellotaped onto the cup. Carrying the drink back to my office, I ended up with splashes of tea over my hand while trying to walk with it.

Drink wise, I could barely taste the tea flavour and it tasted like a much watered down version of TP tea and Ten Ren. The tea kind of reminds me of Hong Kong style milk tea that you get at the local cafes for some reason.

The pearls have a more plastic texture as well, tasting more similar to Gong Cha. If you prefer your pearls super chewy and plasticy then you may like this, but for me, I prefer the pearls with more natural texture and colouring. 

In conclusion, at this price range I expected more since this drink is more expensive here than the equivalents at other bubble tea stores. I guess this store specializes in other types of tea and bubble tea may be something to avoid here.
Signature Assam milk tea is legit

result.name: The Mills

reviews.text: Great renovation of a heritage industrial building. Contemporary arts and heritage textile exhibitions, interesting cultural programming. Nice mix of design shops and selection of cafes, restaurants and bars. Large open air terrace. Very recommended!
Best new place to visit. A renovated mill transformed into a stylish art and shopping complex. Play area for kids, plenty of restaurants, all very modern and delicious.

The Mills is a good example on transforming old factory to new modern shopping mall and office.
The design of The Mills is nice, full of photo spot, with great lighting from outside and outdoor space.  And they also designed open area in the building for exhibitions, which give you spacious feeling.
However, when visiting here, you can see the photos of the old time in here, but you cannot actually tell the usage here, hope this part can be improved

It's a great place for young people, there are a lot of beverage and food outlets and some shops. It's big and spacious shopping area. The great idea is the rooftop garden, public can enjoy the green and open area which is surrounded by industrial building. Interesting experience.

Factory turned art space and museum. Don't miss the Centre for Heritage Arts & Textile on the 2/F which host exhibition. For shops, these 2 interest me most:
- 'alt:' a lab/shop that recycles textiles product. Take your old sweater there and they could produce a new one out of it.
- 'Green Ladies and Green Little' that advocates fashion reuse. 
There are also a few nice cafe which is great for a quiet afternoon.

reviews.text: 貨等太耐

Great renovation of a heritage industrial building. Contemporary arts and heritage textile exhibitions, interesting cultural programming. Nice mix of design shops and selection of cafes, restaurants and bars. Large open air terrace. Very recommended!
感受到南豐的誠意，寬倘的空間，有理念的小店，特色的食店，配合不同的展覽，是一個可讓香港人逃出千篇一律，祇有連鎖奢侈品牌店家的大型商場，可輕鬆地逛上一、兩小時的地方。要好好支持，讓它繼續發展下去。

Tasty! I tried milk tea. You can adjust sugar and ice

唔駛同人逼。飲完走喇隔離啲人都未排到一半買飛。
鐵觀音奶茶加鐵觀音jelly係好正嘅
點了奶霜觀音，奶霜是奶蓋，順滑奶夠香，觀音不及茶湯會香濃，但配上茶味珍珠，非常配合和可口。 值得一讚是沒有冰的，不會因溶冰而淡了。 小弟建議少糖，不太喜歡甜叫半甜。整體是很推薦這家店！
成日行過呢條街，見到呢間都好多人排隊，就索性買一杯飲吓，店員就介紹我飲呢杯翡翠茶那堤又唔會好濃郁而且珍珠亦都好Q彈👍🏿
